SENATE BILL 420
F2 6lr1427
SB 511/25 – EEE CF HB 6
By: Senator M. Washington
Introduced and read first time: January 29, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 4, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Institutions of Higher Education – Pregnant and Parenting Students –
3 Plan and Reporting
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Maryland Higher Education Commission to collect
5 certain data regarding the parental status of students from each public institution
6 of higher education in the State; requiring public institutions of higher education to
7 collect and report certain demographic data from students; requiring all public
8 institutions of higher education to adopt a certain plan for pregnant and parenting
9 students; and generally relating to pregnant and parenting students at public
10 institutions of higher education.
11 BY adding to
12 Article – Education
13 Section 11–409
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
16 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
17 Article – Education
18 Section 15–140
19 Annotated Code of Maryland
20 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
21 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
22 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0420*

2 SENATE BILL 420
1 Article – Education
2 11–409.
3 (A) (1) THE COMMISSION SHALL COLLECT DATA FROM EACH PUBLIC
4 INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION IN THE STATE ON THE PARENTAL STATUS OF
5 STUDENTS ENROLLED IN EACH INSTITUTION.
6 (2) THE COMMISSION, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE PUBLIC
7 INSTITUTIONS OF HIGHER EDUCATION, SHALL DEVELOP QUESTIONS THAT ALLOW
8 EACH STUDENT TO IDENTIFY:
9 (I) WHETHER THE STUDENT IS A PARENT OR A LEGAL
10 GUARDIAN, ACTING AS A PARENT OR A LEGAL GUARDIAN, OR EXERCISING CARE,
11 CUSTODY, OR CONTROL OVER A CHILD OF ANY AGE;
12 (II) THE AGE OF THE CHILDREN FOR WHICH THE STUDENT HAS
13 RESPONSIBILITY; AND
14 (III) THE TYPE OF CAREGIVING RESPONSIBILITIES THE
15 STUDENT PROVIDES, INCLUDING WHETHER THE STUDENT:
16 1. IS A SINGLE PARENT; OR
17 2. SHARES PARENTAL RESPONSIBILITIES WITH
18 SOMEONE IN THE SAME HOUSEHOLD OR A DIFFERENT HOUSEHOLD.
19 (B) (1) EACH PUBLIC INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION SHALL PLACE
20 THE QUESTIONS DEVELOPED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION ON ONE OR
21 MORE FORMS THAT ARE USED BY THE INSTITUTION TO COLLECT DEMOGRAPHIC
22 DATA FROM STUDENTS.
23 (2) EACH PUBLIC INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION SHALL MAKE
24 THE DATA COLLECTED UNDER THIS SECTION AVAILABLE TO THE COMMISSION IN
25 ACCORDANCE WITH THE FORMAT DETERMINED BY THE COMMISSION UNDER
26 SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION.
27 (C) (B) THE COMMISSION SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT
28 THIS SECTION, INCLUDING:
29 (1) ESTABLISHING A COMMON FORMAT AND TIME FRAME FOR THE
30 COLLECTION AND REPORTING OF THE DATA REQUIRED UNDER THIS SECTION; AND

SENATE BILL 420 3
1 (2) REQUIRING THE COLLECTION OF PARENTAL STATUS DATA TO BE
2 INCLUDED WITH THE COLLECTION OF OTHER DEMOGRAPHIC DATA.
3 (D) (C) ON OR BEFORE SEPTEMBER 1, 2027, AND EACH SEPTEMBER 1
4 THEREAFTER, THE COMMISSION SHALL SUBMIT A REPORT TO THE SENATE BUDGET
5 AND TAXATION COMMITTEE, THE SENATE COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION, ENERGY,
6 AND THE ENVIRONMENT, AND THE HOUSE APPROPRIATIONS COMMITTEE, IN
7 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THAT
8 SUMMARIZES THE DATA COLLECTED BY THE COMMISSION UNDER THIS SECTION.
9 15–140.
10 (a) [(1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
11 (2) “Pregnant] IN THIS SECTION, “PREGNANT and parenting student”
12 means a student enrolled at a public [senior higher education] institution OF HIGHER
13 EDUCATION who:
14 [(i)] (1) Is pregnant; [or]
15 [(ii)] (2) Exercises care, custody, or control over a child[.
16 (3) (i) “Public senior higher education institution” means:
17 1. The constituent institutions of the University System of
18 Maryland;
19 2. Morgan State University; and
20 3. St. Mary’s College of Maryland.
21 (ii) “Public senior higher education institution” does not include:
22 1. The University of Maryland Center for Environmental
23 Studies;
24 2. The University of Maryland Global Campus; or
25 3. The University of Baltimore] OF ANY AGE; OR
26 (3) SHARES PARENTAL RESPONSIBILITIES WITH SOMEONE IN
27 THE SAME HOUSEHOLD OR A DIFFERENT HOUSEHOLD.
28 (b) The General Assembly finds that all students at an institution of higher
29 education in the State, regardless of their gender, shall enjoy freedom from discrimination

4 SENATE BILL 420
1 of any kind, including pregnancy discrimination as described in Title IX of the Education
2 Amendments of 1972.
3 (c) (1) Each public [senior higher education] institution OF HIGHER
4 EDUCATION shall adopt a plan regarding pregnant and parenting students that is
5 consistent with Title IX of the federal Higher Education Act.
6 (2) The plan required under paragraph (1) of this subsection shall include:
7 (i) Referral to on–campus or off–campus services to assist regarding
8 the availability of or eligibility for government assistance programs, including:
9 1. The Special Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program
10 for Women, Infants, and Children;
11 2. The Child Care Scholarship Program;
12 3. The Maryland Medical Assistance Program;
13 4. The Maryland Children’s Health Insurance Program; and
14 5. Any other programs, scholarships, or subsidies for
15 pregnant and parenting students;
16 (ii) The provision of information about or referrals to resources
17 regarding adoption services;
18 (iii) The availability of institutional accommodations for pregnant
19 and parenting students; and
20 (iv) (III) A referral network of on–campus and off–campus health
21 care service providers.
22 (d) On or before [August] OCTOBER 1, 2026, each public [senior higher
23 education] institution OF HIGHER EDUCATION shall post the plan adopted under
24 subsection (c) of this section on the institution’s website.
25 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
26 1, 2026.

